.SH NAME
anvil-monitor-lvm \- Tool that watches for changes to LVM devices
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B anvil-monitor-lvm 
\fI\,<command> \/\fR[\fI\,options\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
This tool is meant to be run as a daemon. It will collect data on LVM PVs, VGs and LVs. If a change is detected, 'scan-lvm' will be called. This will keep the Anvil! database up to date with the changes in LVM.
.IP
.SH OPTIONS
\-?, \-h, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show this man page.
.TP
\fB\-\-log\-secure\fR
When logging, record sensitive data, like passwords.
.TP
\-v, \-vv, \-vvv
Set the log level to 1, 2 or 3 respectively. Be aware that level 3 generates a significant amount of log data.
.IP
.SS "Commands:"
This tool takes no switches.
.IP
